1
00:00:15,230 --> 00:00:16,970
Do you believe in karma?

2
00:00:19,130 --> 00:00:21,930
I will never forget the voice that I once heard.

3
00:00:22,270 --> 00:00:23,130
It must've been so funny for you, right?

4
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:26,300
Well, it's not boring.

5
00:00:27,430 --> 00:00:30,170
If it affected you that much,you must have been secretly filmed before?

6
00:00:31,070 --> 00:00:32,630
If you don't have anything nice to say, just don’t say anything.

7
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:36,230
How could you make my Jay trust you so much?

8
00:00:37,070 --> 00:00:41,370
You still don't know the first person who founded Dream was?

9
00:01:09,070 --> 00:01:12,870
I never forced you to go.

10
00:01:15,830 --> 00:01:17,270
We can just live like this.

11
00:01:17,530 --> 00:01:19,800
You can use our baby as an excuse to be together.

12
00:01:20,870 --> 00:01:22,070
No, I'm not signing.

13
00:01:22,570 --> 00:01:23,370
No.

14
00:01:25,900 --> 00:01:26,770
I’m leaving.

15
00:01:27,570 --> 00:01:28,800
You need to sign.

16
00:01:35,370 --> 00:01:36,170
Sign this now.

17
00:01:46,130 --> 00:01:47,630
There’s no need to overreact.

18
00:01:51,930 --> 00:01:53,229
If you don't sign it

19
00:01:54,530 --> 00:01:56,830
then I won’t let you leave this room.

20
00:01:59,900 --> 00:02:00,700
Sign it, will you?

21
00:02:01,930 --> 00:02:03,900
That woman, she's waiting for you, isn't she?

22
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:10,270
Fine.

23
00:02:18,070 --> 00:02:18,870
Are you happy now?

24
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:04,900
Do you have any idea who’s in the car?

25
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:11,270
You’re not fucking looking, didn’t you?

26
00:05:11,970 --> 00:05:12,770
Hey!

27
00:05:18,530 --> 00:05:19,430
Just let him go.

28
00:05:36,970 --> 00:05:37,870
Are you okay?

29
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:39,200
Are you alright?

30
00:05:39,630 --> 00:05:40,430
I’m okay.

31
00:05:40,570 --> 00:05:41,370
Okay?

32
00:05:42,270 --> 00:05:43,070
Yes.

33
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:30,230
Where are you going?

34
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:35,970
I thought that you were sleeping.

35
00:06:36,970 --> 00:06:37,870
So I don't want to bother you.

36
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:49,730
I called you up here.

37
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,470
We haven't even talked yet.

38
00:06:54,330 --> 00:06:55,700
You shouldn’t try to avoid me like that.

39
00:07:02,330 --> 00:07:03,270
You’re really…

40
00:07:05,170 --> 00:07:06,270
really like to ignore me, do you?

41
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:09,900
You like to pretend to be oblivious.

42
00:07:11,130 --> 00:07:12,500
Even though you know damn well that

43
00:07:14,670 --> 00:07:16,630
if you open up to me,

44
00:07:18,470 --> 00:07:20,130
than it is now

45
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,830
You’re talking nonsense again.

46
00:07:27,070 --> 00:07:27,870
See this is exactly you.

47
00:07:29,730 --> 00:07:30,870
You like to push people away,

48
00:07:31,630 --> 00:07:32,930
and also like to say the opposite of what you feel.

49
00:07:34,370 --> 00:07:35,230
Actually,

50
00:07:36,830 --> 00:07:37,900
it’s quite endearing that way.

51
00:07:39,930 --> 00:07:44,300
Although it’s not fun anymore when you keep doing it.

52
00:07:57,270 --> 00:07:57,900
Someday,

53
00:08:00,030 --> 00:08:02,130
you're gonna have to beg me first.

54
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:16,470
Come sleep with me tonight.

55
00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:20,900
What?

56
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:25,130
So we can get a little closer.

57
00:08:29,130 --> 00:08:30,930
And this is my way of repaying you, too.

58
00:08:32,169 --> 00:08:32,970
Whatever I give you,

59
00:08:35,700 --> 00:08:37,200
You'll have to take all of it.

60
00:10:12,330 --> 00:10:13,130
Pavinee,

61
00:10:14,670 --> 00:10:16,030
she had to stay with Jay’s father for Jay's sake.

62
00:10:18,870 --> 00:10:20,370
Until Jay is old enough,

63
00:10:21,230 --> 00:10:23,070
so she decided to divorce her husband.

64
00:10:23,870 --> 00:10:25,200
Then came back to Thailand,

65
00:10:26,770 --> 00:10:28,970
to launch an entertainment business like she’s been dreaming of.

66
00:10:31,870 --> 00:10:35,800
Pavinee herself did not have much knowledge of the Thai entertainment industry.

67
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:38,630
So she needed to rely on the connection of Kongkiat.

68
00:10:39,770 --> 00:10:42,200
Who had more than twenty years of experience in the industry.

69
00:10:43,230 --> 00:10:45,470
At first, everything went well.

70
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:48,630
But after that Kongkiat did something terrible.

71
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:50,630
He betrayed her.

72
00:10:52,170 --> 00:10:57,930
Pavinee, I believe your management
has been causing the company’s losses.

73
00:10:58,670 --> 00:11:00,470
What are your plans with the situation?

74
00:11:03,430 --> 00:11:04,930
I'm sorry, ma’am.

75
00:11:05,470 --> 00:11:06,930
In my perspective,

76
00:11:06,970 --> 00:11:08,170
I really think you should consider

77
00:11:08,430 --> 00:11:11,300
stepping down from the CEO.

78
00:11:11,330 --> 00:11:12,900
And just act as a shareholder of the company,

79
00:11:12,970 --> 00:11:15,470
so that the opportunity is available for people to take your place.

80
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:17,230
Personally, I think that would work better.

81
00:11:21,270 --> 00:11:22,970
For this role in particular,

82
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:25,970
I would like to nominate Mr.Kongkiat.

83
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:30,230
Because I think that he has strong leadership
and management skills.

84
00:11:31,930 --> 00:11:33,230
I think you guys really

85
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:34,970
should just calm down first.

86
00:11:35,330 --> 00:11:36,130
Is everyone agree?

87
00:11:36,230 --> 00:11:36,870
I am.

88
00:11:37,530 --> 00:11:37,970
Me too.

89
00:11:37,970 --> 00:11:41,670
Kongkiat had brought the board members under his influence.

90
00:11:42,130 --> 00:11:47,230
He had convinced everyone
that Pavinee was such an incompetent CEO.

91
00:11:50,130 --> 00:11:54,570
The situation pushed Pavinee to the point that she had
to sell her shares to Kongkiat.

92
00:11:55,970 --> 00:11:58,230
Pavinee felt lost from the betrayal

93
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:02,000
and she already had pretty bad depression at that time.

94
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:04,830
Then she decided to…

95
00:13:39,630 --> 00:13:40,430
So?

96
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:45,000
Do you like my room?

97
00:13:51,530 --> 00:13:52,330
Not at all.

98
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:56,300
It’s so messy just like your secret office.

99
00:13:59,270 --> 00:14:00,070
Really?

100
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:02,800
You don’t like it?

101
00:14:04,770 --> 00:14:05,970
Not even a little impressed by it at all?

102
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:19,370
That old man must’ve told you everything

103
00:14:23,230 --> 00:14:27,570
I was wondering,
why does Sia Jo know so much about you?

104
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:33,600
He told you so much about me,

105
00:14:34,670 --> 00:14:36,100
why didn't he just tell you everything at once

106
00:14:39,900 --> 00:14:40,770
What do you mean?

107
00:14:44,770 --> 00:14:45,500
The first person

108
00:14:47,130 --> 00:14:48,730
that called me when my mother jumped off the building

109
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:50,630
was him,

110
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:53,870
Uncle Jo.

111
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:01,000
Uncle?

112
00:15:01,670 --> 00:15:02,470
Aright.

113
00:15:04,630 --> 00:15:05,870
Aren't you wondering?

114
00:15:07,770 --> 00:15:09,470
Why am I a partner,

115
00:15:10,430 --> 00:15:12,630
and have an office in Alice’s.

116
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:23,730
So the people of Dream, they don't know you're the founder’s son?

117
00:15:26,730 --> 00:15:28,570
My mother and I had different last names.

118
00:15:30,970 --> 00:15:33,270
When Mom divorced my Dad and came back to Thailand,

119
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,230
no one knows what her son looked like.

120
00:15:40,430 --> 00:15:42,200
Then I used my fancy degree that I graduated from abroad at my advance

121
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:45,600
and also with the help of the vice president who is loyal to my mom,

122
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:49,670
so I was able to get a job there easily as an executive director.

123
00:15:57,530 --> 00:15:58,600
Wanna to eat something?

124
00:16:02,100 --> 00:16:02,900
No.

125
00:16:06,130 --> 00:16:06,930
Steak?

126
00:16:08,630 --> 00:16:09,430
Salad?

127
00:16:11,870 --> 00:16:13,030
Or spaghetti?

128
00:16:15,770 --> 00:16:19,930
Or do you only prefer to eat Pad-Thai?

129
00:16:22,830 --> 00:16:24,770
If you want to eat that, I'll order it.

130
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:27,200
Do you want it?

131
00:16:35,170 --> 00:16:36,830
How many days have you not been sleeping?

132
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:40,700
Two days.

133
00:16:42,730 --> 00:16:43,530
No.

134
00:16:45,100 --> 00:16:45,900
Three days.

135
00:16:48,900 --> 00:16:49,700
Three days?

136
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:51,770
Are you worried about me?

137
00:16:54,970 --> 00:16:55,770
Where's the bedroom?

138
00:16:56,670 --> 00:16:57,570
So what do you want to eat?

139
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,000
I don't want to eat.

140
00:17:00,170 --> 00:17:00,970
Nope.

141
00:17:03,870 --> 00:17:05,569
I’m going to cook for you.

142
00:17:07,599 --> 00:17:08,700
You have to eat mine.

143
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:17,569
You're this sleepy but still insist on cooking for me?

144
00:17:18,599 --> 00:17:19,670
You need to go to bed now.

145
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:20,800
Do you eat anything?

146
00:17:21,369 --> 00:17:22,170
Go sleep now.

147
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:23,700
Come on, just eat something.

148
00:17:24,329 --> 00:17:25,430
I’m not, you need sleep.

149
00:17:30,670 --> 00:17:31,470
I have a question.

150
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:37,130
When your mother and brother died,

151
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:42,270
did you cry at all?

152
00:17:56,270 --> 00:17:57,100
Go to sleep now.

153
00:17:57,830 --> 00:17:59,330
Are you not really hungry?

154
00:18:02,870 --> 00:18:03,300
Sleep now.

155
00:18:04,400 --> 00:18:05,000
Go to bed.

156
00:18:06,330 --> 00:18:06,630
Come on.

157
00:18:06,970 --> 00:18:07,770
Sleep, right?

158
00:18:14,600 --> 00:18:15,730
What are you doing?

159
00:18:29,530 --> 00:18:30,800
What the hell are you doing?

160
00:18:34,230 --> 00:18:35,830
What are you trying to do?

161
00:18:44,930 --> 00:18:45,630
Hey?

162
00:18:47,100 --> 00:18:47,900
You?

163
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:52,930
Dummy?

164
00:18:59,530 --> 00:19:00,430
At least you’re able to sleep.

165
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:04,530
You’re so damn heavy.

166
00:20:38,300 --> 00:20:39,100
Ouch!

167
00:20:40,430 --> 00:20:41,330
So damn heavy.

168
00:21:12,270 --> 00:21:17,870
Venice, a young actor with a panic attack when there’s a camera facing him.

169
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:04,200
Yes?

170
00:22:21,770 --> 00:22:24,700
How do you know that I am here?

171
00:22:26,430 --> 00:22:28,370
My debtor is a lot harder to find than you.

172
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:37,870
We need to talk.

173
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:46,070
If you’re here to tell me to go back to Dream’s,

174
00:22:46,770 --> 00:22:47,600
you’re wasting your time here.

175
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:49,100
I'm not going back.

176
00:22:51,470 --> 00:22:54,900
There's nothing I can do now
in the entertainment industry.

177
00:22:57,170 --> 00:22:58,430
Which means you don't want to know

178
00:22:59,230 --> 00:23:01,400
who ruined your audition?

179
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:10,070
You mean…

180
00:23:11,070 --> 00:23:12,370
someone did that to me on purpose?

181
00:23:13,970 --> 00:23:15,370
If you want to know the truth,

182
00:23:16,800 --> 00:23:19,470
today at five P.M., I’ll see you at studio sixty-seven.

183
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:23,200
If you're willing to go there,

184
00:23:25,700 --> 00:23:26,530
you’ll find out.

185
00:23:34,970 --> 00:23:36,200
Look at you now.

186
00:23:42,670 --> 00:23:43,870
If you don't care about me,

187
00:23:44,930 --> 00:23:47,800
at least care about someone who genuinely cares about you, like P'Kajorn.

188
00:24:11,730 --> 00:24:12,530
Hello?

189
00:24:15,470 --> 00:24:17,600
You go and wait in the toilet behind Studio Sixty Seven.

190
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:25,330
Gus, is the coffee for Sunny ready yet?

191
00:24:25,370 --> 00:24:26,200
Not yet. I'll go look it.

192
00:24:27,370 --> 00:24:29,730
Do you have a light roast Ethiopian coffee bean?

193
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:30,800
No, we don’t.

194
00:24:30,970 --> 00:24:32,670
Next time, you need to have it stand by.

195
00:24:33,370 --> 00:24:34,970
How about this new bean first?

196
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:38,100
Stop it, whatever Sunny wants, he shall have it.

197
00:24:42,530 --> 00:24:43,330
Excuse me?

198
00:24:45,700 --> 00:24:48,200
I am a huge fan of Sunny.

199
00:24:48,530 --> 00:24:49,330
Yes?

200
00:24:50,130 --> 00:24:53,730
Uhm.. Can you give this letter to Sunny?

201
00:24:56,130 --> 00:24:58,770
I didn’t know that Sunny has such a cute fan boy.

202
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:01,000
Okay, I'll handle it.

203
00:25:01,430 --> 00:25:02,230
Thank you.

204
00:25:02,300 --> 00:25:03,100
You're welcome.

205
00:25:09,270 --> 00:25:10,270
Close your eyes.

206
00:25:13,300 --> 00:25:14,870
Can you check if you like the look?

207
00:25:15,570 --> 00:25:16,370
Very handsome.

208
00:25:17,670 --> 00:25:18,470
Clear skin.

209
00:25:19,970 --> 00:25:20,830
Are you okay with the makeup?

210
00:25:20,900 --> 00:25:21,700
Okay?

211
00:25:21,870 --> 00:25:22,770
Momma, let’s go eat.

212
00:25:32,270 --> 00:25:33,230
Where's my coffee?

213
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:37,870
They couldn’t find it here but
I have someone getting it now.

214
00:25:39,430 --> 00:25:40,700
Next time, write it down alright?

215
00:25:41,130 --> 00:25:42,430
So they know what kind of coffee I usually drink,

216
00:25:43,100 --> 00:25:45,700
it’s annoying that I have to tell you repeatedly.

217
00:25:48,200 --> 00:25:49,000
Right.

218
00:25:50,070 --> 00:25:53,570
Oh, there's a fan asking me to give you this letter.

219
00:25:54,500 --> 00:25:55,830
Here?

220
00:25:56,700 --> 00:25:58,570
How does he know that I’m here?

221
00:25:59,300 --> 00:26:00,630
I don't even know if he's a sasaeng or not?

222
00:26:01,270 --> 00:26:02,170
How dare you accept it?

223
00:26:03,300 --> 00:26:04,930
I don’t think that he’s a sasaeng,

224
00:26:05,100 --> 00:26:06,670
since he just stopped by and left.

225
00:26:07,470 --> 00:26:09,900
He’s a very cute looking fan boy.

226
00:26:12,300 --> 00:26:13,270
Here's the letter.

227
00:26:20,600 --> 00:26:21,470
Close the door on your way out.

228
00:26:33,830 --> 00:26:34,970
I have proof that you ruined my audition.

229
00:26:34,970 --> 00:26:36,330
If you don't want anyone to find out about it,

230
00:26:36,330 --> 00:26:37,770
meet me at the restroom behind the building.

231
00:27:03,870 --> 00:27:05,130
So it’s really you.

232
00:27:07,330 --> 00:27:08,730
So you're going to rat me out?

233
00:27:10,370 --> 00:27:11,170
Fine.

234
00:27:11,700 --> 00:27:12,670
I’d love to see you try.

235
00:27:13,100 --> 00:27:13,900
Loser!

236
00:27:16,530 --> 00:27:18,570
I don't know what proof you have

237
00:27:19,330 --> 00:27:20,700
but I'm not afraid of you.

238
00:27:21,670 --> 00:27:24,300
You are both stupid and couldn't act in front of a camera.

239
00:27:25,570 --> 00:27:27,370
Although you have the gut to threaten me?

240
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:28,970
Wait a minute, P’Sunny.

241
00:27:29,270 --> 00:27:30,370
I don't know what you're talking about.

242
00:27:30,430 --> 00:27:31,170
Liar!

243
00:27:32,970 --> 00:27:34,800
If you dare call me here like this,

244
00:27:36,170 --> 00:27:39,370
next time it won't just be the camera.

245
00:27:42,470 --> 00:27:43,270
Camera?

246
00:27:44,930 --> 00:27:48,230
So the camera in the audition room was all you?

247
00:27:50,230 --> 00:27:51,400
Why did you do that?

248
00:27:53,230 --> 00:27:54,330
What are you talking about?

249
00:27:56,030 --> 00:27:57,500
Didn’t you tell me that you have proof?

250
00:27:58,170 --> 00:27:59,170
What proof are you talking about?

251
00:27:59,800 --> 00:28:00,670
Where is it? Give it to me now.

252
00:28:00,700 --> 00:28:02,070
What are you talking about? I don't know.

253
00:28:03,270 --> 00:28:04,630
Are you messing with me?

254
00:28:06,300 --> 00:28:07,370
Who do you think you are?

255
00:28:07,670 --> 00:28:08,830
You're messing with the wrong guy here.

256
00:28:10,100 --> 00:28:11,400
If I want anything,

257
00:28:11,600 --> 00:28:12,970
or I want to get rid of anyone,

258
00:28:13,770 --> 00:28:15,930
I can just call someone and it’ll be done.

259
00:28:17,100 --> 00:28:18,100
Next time, If you still dare to do this

260
00:28:19,670 --> 00:28:20,930
you’ll be dead for sure.

261
00:29:18,600 --> 00:29:21,730
What Sunny did to you was that bad?

262
00:29:22,530 --> 00:29:25,500
He’s fleeing just because he’s seeing you.

263
00:29:27,330 --> 00:29:28,130
See that?

264
00:29:33,270 --> 00:29:34,070
Yes.

265
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:39,070
It's really what you told me.

266
00:29:48,570 --> 00:29:49,970
There's a movie script

267
00:29:51,100 --> 00:29:53,500
where the character has a panic attack in front of the camera.

268
00:29:55,630 --> 00:29:58,030
I think you would understand this character very well.

269
00:29:59,170 --> 00:30:01,700
So I already asked P’Kajorn to get you the script from the director

270
00:30:06,100 --> 00:30:08,300
It's on you now whether you will take it

271
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:10,800
or not.

272
00:30:16,600 --> 00:30:17,400
If you’re saying no to it.

273
00:30:18,470 --> 00:30:20,730
What you're gonna lose isn't just an acting career,

274
00:30:22,870 --> 00:30:24,900
but also the opportunity to get revenge.

